result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota Darrell Strebig was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Request for Payment Plan, Agreement to Make Payments, and Order

Defendant Dakota Darrell Strebig in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Tlusty placed joint recommendation on the record.  Victim notification has been complied with.  DE entered a plea of no contest to Count 1.  Plea colloquy.  Court found plea given freely, voluntarily, and intelligently; accepted plea, found DE guilty and entered judgment of conviction.  Court imposed on Count 1: court costs, DNA sample and surcharge.  Court dismissed but read in Count 2.  Payment plan set at $100/month commencing 1-15-16. ba
Order for Appearance at Settlement Conference; Report to Court on Results of Settlement Conference.

Defendant Dakota Darrell Strebig in court, in custody.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant believed that Attorney Nocco was representing him.  Attorney Tlusty is indicating that Attorney Nocco is representing the defendant on another case.  Court indicated to the defendant that he must call the public defender's office to have Attorney Nocco appointed to this case.  Defendant waives the reading of the complaint, charges and penalties.  Court enters a plea of not guilty to the charges.  Bond continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for December 10, 2015 at 10:00 am.  - rt

Defendant shall not leave the State of Wisconsin without prior notice to and written approval of the court. Defendant shall comply with booking procedures at the Taylor County Sheriff's Department. Defendant shall have no contact with D.K.M. dob: 8-24-98.
